OL,3,CFrom Wakefield under-10s to Wembley:
OL,4,CCup final ref's 'nerves'
OL,6,F"Then I refereed a game at Yorkshire
OL,7,FAmateurs in Leeds and I turned up on
OL,8,Fthis particular day and I remember
OL,9,Fseeing a programme and it had my name
OL,10,Fin it. And I remember I could hear the
OL,11,Fturnstiles clicking around and I could
OL,12,Fhear the music being played before the
OL,13,Fgame and there was a part of me that
OL,14,Fwas like: I've made it."
OL,16,FMadley's younger brother and fellow
OL,17,Freferee, Bobby, congratulated him on
OL,18,Fbeing chosen for the final in a post
OL,19,Fon X saying "Dad would be so proud",
OL,20,Fin reference to their father who died
OL,21,Fin 2011.
